When someone seeks their soul mate and you joke about the silliness of the concept, that's not a promising sign!

You've already found your soul mate or remain open to the possibility.

If you measure love in dollars, the first date might cost a fortune. With all that smooching and spending, is it any wonder love makes you feel worn out? When someone seeks their soul mate and you joke about the silliness of the concept, that's not a promising sign!

answersResultList.title: You hold back your love.
answersResultList.resultContent: To you, intimacy equals vulnerability or weakness. Maybe you claim you've never been in love or don't know what love is. You scoff at the idea of soul mates. You feel nervous and lost in the grip of a deep attraction or reckless emotion. On your first date, you'd rather hang with a group of friends than risk being alone together. You might make a romantic interest feel unimportant.

answersResultList.title: You don't have a love flaw.
answersResultList.resultContent: You're a well-integrated personality in control of your issues or neuroses. You know love is different from like and desire, because you've been there once or twice. You've already found your soul mate or remain open to the possibility.
